reviewText: I love this video and watch it whenever I start to get into a funk about my personal value. I love what she had to say about the Patriarchy, men and vulnerability, and the things that make us uncomfortable. Plus all the great stuff we love to hear from her. I am not letting my copy out of my hands even for a viewing. I bought it years ago and I wouldn't sell it even for profit. I saw it in out patient therapy and it helped me with my mental recovery process. The clinician who gave it one star didn't realize it's a collector's item not  a packaged project. That one star is therefore not applicable. It's a lecture, professionally recorded with good lighting & sound quality. Totally worth watching. Repeatedly

Not impressed, for $100, Luckily I got it on sale for $55 but its not worth that. One can google her youtube videos and get as much if not more information. I thought it was something I could show therapy groups, as it was priced like it was an actual video I could show clients. But nope, it was an impulse buy for sure and I will be more careful from now on!
I love her work.  It's easy to understand and there are also useful options for application of her work.
This DVD is an excellent intro to the topic of shame for men and women. Everyone can benefit for this message.

I use this DVD in my groups.  It is powerful.  I love it.  I lent my copy out and it never
Returned.  Help me!
I keep ordering this video then giving it to someone and now I don't have a copy!  Please bring back more.  Great speaker, uplifting, great sense of humor.
